  "body": "I've set the `gas` to `300_000` and `gasPrice` to `1e11` in `localhost` - `networks`:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nnetworks: {\r\n...\r\nlocalhost: {\r\n      url: 'http://localhost:8545',\r\n      gas: 300_000,\r\n      gasPrice: 1e11,\r\n    },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter this config set, I `deploy` a contract which will not cost more than 300_000 gas on hardhat network.\r\nThe fact was the `gasPrice` works, it's `100Gwei` in transaction info, but the gas limit is still estimated gas, not `300_000`.\r\nThis prevents me from simply creating a data-perfect, replayable contract deployment transaction using Hardhat's deploy method.",
